        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Numbers 21<ref n="1" target="#Num-021-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor"
                             /></title>
                        <l n="1">And
                            <milestone unit="page" n="248v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             all the congregation saw that Aaron passed away, and they wept for him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             thirty days, all the house of Israel.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="2">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             the Canaanite, king of Arad, who dwelt in the south, heard
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             that Israel came <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-021-seg001_trl"
                             />by the way of spies<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Num-021-seg001_trl" /><ref n="2" target="#Num-021-fn2_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> and he fought against Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             and took some of them captive.</l>
                        <l n="3">And Israel vowed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             a vow to the Lord, and said, ‘If you will indeed give this
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             people into my hand, then I will devote
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             their cities |to destruction|.’</l>
                        <l n="4">And the Lord listened to the voice
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             of Israel, and gave |over| the Canaanites, and he devoted them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and their cities |to destruction|. And he called the name of the place
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             Hormah.</l>
                        <l n="5">And they set out from mount Hor by the way of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             Red Sea, to go around the land of Edom. And the soul of the people got
                            tired
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             on the way.</l>
                        <l n="6">And the people spoke about God
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             and about Moses, saying, ‘Why have you brought us out from Egypt
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             to die in the wilderness? Because there is no bread, and there is no
                            water,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             and our soul is tired of this worthless bread.’</l>
                        <l n="7">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             the Lord sent fiery serpents among the people,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             and they bit the people, and many people of Israel died.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="8">And the people came to Moses, and said,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             ‘We have sinned, because we have spoken about the Lord and about you.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             Pray to the Lord, that he shall take away the serpents from us.’
                            <milestone unit="page" n="249r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             And Moses prayed for the people.</l>
                        <l n="9">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             the Lord said to Moses, ‘Make you a fiery serpent and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             set it on a standard. And it shall be, that everyone who is bitten
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             by a serpent and he looks on it, he will recover.</l>
                        <l n="10">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             And Moses made a bronze serpent and put it on a standard,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             and it was, if a serpent bit a man, then
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             he would look at the bronze serpent and recover.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="11">And the children of Israel set out and camped
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             in Oboth.</l>
                        <l n="12">And they set out from Oboth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and camped <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-021-seg002_trl" />at the
                            meadows of encampments<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="Num-021-seg002_trl" /><ref n="3" target="#Num-021-fn3_trl"
                                type="noteAnchor" />, in the wilderness
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             which is opposite Moab, toward the sun’s rising.</l>
                        <l n="13">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             From there they set out and camped in the |valley of| the river
                            Zered.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="14">From there they set out and camped across the ford
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             of Arnon which is in the wilderness that extends from the border of the
                            Amorites,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             because Arnon was the border of Moab, between Moab and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             the Amorites.</l>
                        <l n="15">Therefore it is said in the Book
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             of the Wars of the Lord: Waheb in Suphah and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             rivers of Arnon,</l>
                        <l n="16">And the riverbed of the rivers
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             that he placed down to the dwelling of Ar, and leans to the border
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             of Moab.</l>
                        <l n="17">And from there they set out to Beer: that is
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             the well of which the Lord spoke to Moses, ‘Gather the people
                            <milestone unit="page" n="249v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             together, so that I may give them water.’</l>
                        <l n="18">Then
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             Israel sang this song, saying, ‘Lift up,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             oh well, your waters, we sing to it.</l>
                        <l n="19">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             The rulers dug the well, the nobles of the people dug it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             with the one who gives statues, with their own staffs.’ And from the
                            wilderness
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             they set out to Mattanah.</l>
                        <l n="20">And from Mattanah
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             they set out to Nahaliel. And from Nahaliel to Bamoth.</l>
                        <l n="21">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             And from Bamoth they set out to <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-021-seg003_trl" />a place called
                                <emph>Gay</emph><anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-021-seg003_trl"
                                 /><ref n="4" target="#Num-021-fn4_trl" type="noteAnchor" /> that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             is in the field of Moab, <seg type="commented"
                                corresp="#Num-021-seg004_trl" />to the top of the summit<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="Num-021-seg004_trl" /><ref n="5"
                                target="#Num-021-fn5_trl" type="noteAnchor" />, which appears
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             before Jeshimon<ref n="6" target="#Num-021-fn6_trl" type="noteAnchor"
                             />.</l>
                        <l n="22">And Israel sent envoys
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             to Sihon, king of the Amorites, saying,</l>
                        <l n="23">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             ‘Let me pass through your land. We will not turn at a field and at a
                            vineyard,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             and we will not drink well waters. We will go by the king’s road,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             until we pass your border.’</l>
                        <l n="24">And Sihon did not empower
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             Israel to pass through his land. And Sihon gathered
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             all his people together, and went out against Israel
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             to the wilderness. And he came to Jahaz and fought
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             against Israel.</l>
                        <l n="25">And Israel killed him by the edge of the sword
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             and inherited his land from Arnon to Jabbok,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             to the children of Ammon, because the border of the children of Ammon
                            was strong:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#Num-021-seg005_trl" />for that reason
                            the Amorites could not take more from the land of the children
                            <milestone unit="page" n="250r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             of Ammon<anchor type="commented" xml:id="Num-021-seg005_trl" /><ref
                                n="7" target="#Num-021-fn7_trl" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="26">And Israel took all these cities,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             and Israel lived in all the cities of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             Amorites, in Heshbon, and in all its villages,</l>
                        <l n="27">Because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             Heshbon was the city of Sihon, he is the king of the Amorites, and he
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             had fought against the first king of Moab and taken all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             his land from his hand, as far as Arnon.</l>
                        <l n="28">On account of this
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             the ones who say proverbs used to say, ‘Come to Heshbon,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             let the city of Sihon be built and organized.</l>
                        <l n="29">For fire
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             went out of Heshbon, a flame from the city of Sihon. It consumed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             the city called Ar of Moab, the lords of the hills
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             of Arnon.</l>
                        <l n="30">Woe unto you, Moab: You have perished,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             people of Chemosh. He has made his sons fugitives and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             has given his daughters into captivity to the king of Amorites, to
                            Sihon.</l>
                        <l n="31">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             when we have shot at them with arrows, then the reign of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             Heshbon has perished, as far as Dibon, and we have desolated them as
                            far as Nophah
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             which is as far as Medeba.’</l>
                        <l n="32">And Israel lived in the land
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             of the Amorites.</l>
                        <l n="33">And Moses sent to spy out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             Jazer, and they captured its villages and destroyed the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             Amorites that were there.</l>
                        <l n="34">And they turned and went up
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             by the way of Bashan, and Og, king of Bashan, went out against
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             them, he, and all his people, to the war of Edrei.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="250v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="35">And the Lord said to Moses, ‘Do not fear him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             because I will give him and all his people and his land into your hand,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and you shall do to him as you did to Sihon, king of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             Amorites, who loved at Heshbon.’</l>
                        <l n="36">And they defeated him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             and his sons and all his people until he did not have a remnant left,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             and they inherited his land.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="37">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             And the children of Israel set out and camped in the meadows
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             of Moab across the ford of Jordan of Jericho.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            <emph>Parashat Balak</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                    </ab>
                </div>
